DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$b = non_zero_random(-8,8,2);
$a = random(3,11,2);
$m = -$b/$a;
$ans = "-$b/$a x + $b";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 20:
$BR $PACE $BR
Find an equation for the linear function which has $BITALIC y ${EITALIC}-intercept $b and $BITALIC x ${EITALIC}-intercept $a.
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( f(x) = \ \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
END_TEXT

ANS(fun_cmp($ans,vars=>'x'));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR
$BBOLD SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
Since we know the $BITALIC x${EITALIC}-intercept and $BITALIC y${EITALIC}-intercept are ($a , 0) and (0 , $b) respectively, we can find the slope:
\[ \mbox{slope} = m = \frac{$b - 0}{0 - $a} = - \frac{$b}{$a} \]
$BR
We can then put the slope and the $BITALIC y${EITALIC}-intercept into the general slope-intercept form for a line:
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( f(x) = -\frac{$b}{$a} x + $b \)
$BR
END_SOLUTION
      
ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.